-- Brazil Agriculture Ministry Says Prices for White and Raw Sugar to Drop
-- Lucia Kassai
-- 2010-07-28T14:24:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/brazil-agriculture-ministry-says-prices-for-white-and-raw-sugar-to-drop.html

          
          
             Brazil’s Agriculture Ministry said
raw and white sugar prices will fall over the next two years.  
 White sugar will decline to $490 a ton by 2011 from $540
now, while raw sugar will drop to $390 a ton from $480 now, Luis
Job, coordinator of the ministry’s sugar and ethanol department,
said today in an e-mailed statement.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucia Kassai in Sao Paulo at 
 lkassai@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        